The answer seems to be A. You can actually design a vmss with a public IP in each vm. This is what I found on Microsoft docs => To create a virtual machine scale set that assigns a public IP address to each VM, make sure the API version of the Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachineScaleSets resource is 2017-03-30, and add a publicipaddressconfiguration JSON packet to the scale set ipConfigurations section. Example: 
"publicipaddressconfiguration": {
 "name": "pub1",
 "properties": {
 "idleTimeoutInMinutes": 15
 }
 }

Link - https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machine-scale-sets/virtual-machine-scale-sets-faq
